The paper discusses real-time search methods for autonomous agents, which involves planning and learning in real-time environments. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper's focus on heuristic search algorithms and their control parameters suggests that cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG and cs.SY. The mention of scalability and ad hoc sensor networks also suggests a potential connection to distributed systems (cs.DC) or networking (cs.NI), but these are less likely given the paper's primary focus on real-time search algorithms.
